The paper deals with extractive summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of entity relationship graphs and linguistic typology suggests a focus on NLP techniques and applications. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The use of keyword identification and information retrieval techniques also suggests a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of machine learning and the development of a hybrid model suggest a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of human raters to evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed method suggests a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
